<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="22" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="22">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="22">
Sometimes the collection from French Guiana-J.B. Aublet s.n. (BM [scan!], LINN SM-374.5 [microfiche!], P-Rousseau 5: 181! [acquired by P only in 1953])-is cited as the type of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Aphrophoridae" genus="Cordia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nodosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">Cordia nodosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Aphrophoridae" genus="Cordia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirsuta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">Cordia hirsuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In fact it is unlikely that 
<bibRefCitation author="Lamarck, JB" pageId="4" pageNumber="23" publicationUrl="10.5962/bhl.title.824" refId="B9" refString="Lamarck, JB, 1792. Tableau Encyclopedique et Methodique des Trois Regnes de la Nature, Botanique tome 1, vol. 2, part 1. Panckoucke, Paris, 353-440. ., 10.5962/bhl.title.824" title="Tableau Encyclopedique et Methodique des Trois Regnes de la Nature, Botanique tome 1, vol. 2, part 1. Panckoucke, Paris, 353 - 440." url="10.5962/bhl.title.824" year="1792">Lamarck (1792</bibRefCitation>
, 1, 2(1): 422) or 
<bibRefCitation author="Willdenow, CL" journalOrPublisher="Novon" pageId="4" pageNumber="23" publicationUrl="10.5962/bhl.title.60064" refId="B18" refString="Willdenow, CL, 1798. Species Plantarum , ed. 4, 1(2). Nauk, Berlin, 1-1070. ., 10.5962/bhl.title.60064" title="Species Plantarum, ed. 4, 1 (2). Nauk, Berlin, 1 - 1070." url="10.5962/bhl.title.60064" year="1798">Willdenow (1798</bibRefCitation>
, 1(2): 1076) saw a specimen as they only cited Aublet plate 86.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="22">Aublet s.n. can be seen at http://plants.jstor.org/specimen/bm000906214</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="22">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Aphrophoridae" genus="Cordia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirsuta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">Cordia hirsuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
